parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the AEB system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if other vehicles are following closely.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes without warning
even when there is no obstacle or hazard present.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Malfunction of Forward Collision Warning (FCW) and Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) Systems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the FCW and AEB systems can lead to a failure to alert the driver of potential collisions or prevent accidents, increasing the risk of crashes and injuries.
symptoms: The FCW and AEB systems fail to activate when needed
leading to confusion and uncertainty for the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unreliable Chassis Control System can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard
such as "Chassis Control System Error See Owner's Manual
" and the vehicle may experience reduced braking performance or uncontrolled sliding.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unexplained Activation of Reverse Sensors and Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexplained activation of the reverse sensors and braking system can cause unexpected stops or jerking movements, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud noise and stops suddenly when reversing
even when there is no obstacle present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuators can cause the doors to remain unlocked, compromising the safety and security of the vehicle's occupants and their belongings.
symptoms: The doors do not lock or unlock when using the lock/unlock switch inside the door

or the button on the outside of the door handle; the doors remain in the same position (locked or unlocked) even when attempting to change the lock status; the automatic door lock feature when driving does not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic emergency braking system can increase the risk of accidents, as the vehicle may not stop or slow down in emergency situations, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The automatic emergency braking system warning light illuminates; the vehicle fails to stop or slow down in emergency situations; the system becomes defective due to environmental factors such as rainstorms.
